{
  "stem": "10588.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to continue the story, so when we went to work, what made it harder was that, first of all, it was, at that point, was not useful work.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we could carry the same stone back and forth just to wear us out, to mock us, and to, to, you know, to have-- give them a chance-- their sadism to come up.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Secondly, if one fell or whatever, we couldn't-- we're not allowed to help each other openly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did it in, in hiding, but not openly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We could not speak on, on the-- so we had hardly any control.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For instance, like, we didn't have water to wash.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we used to go, just to feel the-- go through the motions sometimes in the morning.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I used to do that because I was used every morning to wash, you know, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And still would say, in the morning, the prayers, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And at night, even I had no longer my family to say it with me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But to try as much as I could, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So physically, I was totally enslaved.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I had no control of life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Spiritually, I could think and feel what I wanted.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I remember one time when I was in Auschwitz, and I felt the burden, the bitter taste of slavery.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I felt, if I would have a pencil and paper now, I would write a poem.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But there was no pencil and paper.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I told you, my earthly possessions were what I wore and the bowl, the enamel bowl from which we got the soup.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I wrote a poem in my, in my head.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I was liberated, when I came here to America, of course, I couldn't speak a word of English.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was constant adjusting from one to the other.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was among my first poems, and I would like to share it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'I feel like a bird with clipped wings tied to this earth by invisible strings, chained to a destiny I did not choose.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I feel like a prisoner that cannot break loose.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I look at the sky with a heavy sigh, but my wings have been clipped, and I can no longer fly.' Then I realized that the concept of freedom is a bird in flight and not in a bird in a cage.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I pledged to myself, if I'll get out, I will never use brute force.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I will never try to force somebody to do something, but neither will I allow other people to do it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I understood the concept of freedom.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I understood what my forefathers, what the, the Jews in Egypt, the Israelites in Egypt, must have felt like.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I realized that there is no substitute for personal experience, from knowledge derived from personal experience.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I realized then that nothing in the world, no textbook, no professor, not the best college, could teach me what my experience taught me.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Because I had to-- I got to know myself, who I am, how much I could endure, how much I could understand, how much I could feel, and what I've became, and saw the world through a completely different things.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because I was thinking, Mengele was a university-educated man with doctoral degrees.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He had the ability to heal the, the sick, and perversely, he choosed to, to kill the, the healthy imprisoned in Auschwitz, more than 400,000 Jews, [NON-ENGLISH], were murdered because of him, the selections, to the left, to the right.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I realized the power of words, how words can heal and, and kill, how it is.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I started-- everything was the reverse.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It, it was, it was amazing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And all the things that I'd been taught all my life and everything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then, this same Mengele [INAUDIBLE] was such a sadist.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He would take, make, you know, select people and would make operations with people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And some men were castrated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I personally know somebody who lives in Israel who will never, never had a family because he was castrated.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Some didn't survive experiments without, without, without anesthesia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this I was told by people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If I would have seen, then I would have been one of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Same like with the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If I would have seen the inside of gas chambers, I wouldn't be here to tell you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But how do I know?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because what I found out later.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I didn't know at the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You see what the Nazis did, is that they selected, they selected people.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was called the Sonderkommando, men who work there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they, after three months, they know that they should not, if they survive, they shouldn't survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They shouldn't tell what's happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They wanted to destroy, not to have witness.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
